---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Header from '../../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../../components/Footer.astro';
import JournalSubNav from '../../components/JournalSubNav.astro';
---
<BaseLayout title="Best British Schools in Hong Kong — Journal" description="A guide to Hong Kong's top-ranked British curriculum schools, covering fees, debentures, curricula, and what parents should know.">
  <Header slot="header" />

  <JournalSubNav active="Cities" />

  <!-- HERO -->
  <section class="relative w-full h-[60vh] min-h-[400px] overflow-hidden">
    <img
      src="/images/hong-kong-hero.jpg"
      alt="Victoria Harbour, Hong Kong"
      class="absolute inset-0 w-full h-full object-cover"
    />
    <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-gradient-to-t from-black/70 via-black/30 to-transparent"></div>
    <div class="absolute bottom-0 left-0 right-0 p-6 md:p-12">
      <div class="bsa-container max-w-2xl">
        <p class="label text-white/70 mb-4">Cities</p>
        <h1 class="text-white text-3xl md:text-5xl leading-tight">Best British Schools in Hong Kong</h1>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ARTICLE BODY -->
  <article class="section">
    <div class="container-narrow">
      <p class="font-body text-black/50 text-sm mb-8">Updated April 2026 &middot; 5 min read</p>

      <div class="space-y-6 font-body text-black/80 leading-relaxed">
        <p>
          Hong Kong has seven British curriculum schools in the British Schools Asia index. The market is unusually deep — the city sits alongside the English Schools Foundation (ESF) system and a long tail of international schools running other curricula. Annual Year 3 tuition at our indexed schools ranges from approximately USD 18,400 to USD 33,900, with debenture costs at some schools adding a significant one-off expense.
        </p>

        <p>
          <a href="/schools/hong-kong/hong-kong/kellett-school">Kellett School</a> leads the city ranking. A not-for-profit British school founded in 1976 by parents seeking British-style education, Kellett enrols around 1,550 students across campuses in Pok Fu Lam and Kowloon Bay. The pathway is a clean ENC through GCSE/IGCSE to A Levels — one of the purer British routes in the city. The school holds BSO Outstanding accreditation across all categories from its 2023 inspection.
        </p>

        <p>
          <a href="/schools/hong-kong/hong-kong/yew-chung-international-school-hong-kong">Yew Chung International School of Hong Kong</a>, founded in 1932, is one of Hong Kong's oldest international schools, enrolling approximately 2,200 students across three campuses in Kowloon Tong. The school's distinctive feature is its bilingual co-teacher model, pairing Western and Chinese educators in the same classroom from the earliest years. ENC is followed through Year 11, then the IB Diploma in sixth form.
        </p>

        <p>
          <a href="/schools/hong-kong/hong-kong/german-swiss-international-school">German Swiss International School</a> opened in 1969 and runs two parallel streams under one roof: an English Stream following ENC + IGCSE + IB Diploma, and a German Stream culminating in the German International Abitur. The main campus is on The Peak with a separate Kindergarten in Pok Fu Lam.
        </p>

        <p>
          <a href="/schools/hong-kong/hong-kong/harrow-international-school-hong-kong">Harrow International School Hong Kong</a> opened in 2012 in So Kwun Wat, Tuen Mun, and is the only Hong Kong school in our index offering boarding. Approximately 1,300 students are enrolled. The pathway is ENC through IGCSE to A Levels, with a Capital Levy on top of annual tuition.
        </p>

        <p>
          <a href="/schools/hong-kong/hong-kong/nord-anglia-international-school-hong-kong">Nord Anglia International School Hong Kong</a> opened in 2014 and operates across multiple campuses in Lam Tin, Kwun Tong and Sai Kung. ENC progresses to IGCSE and either A Levels or the IB Diploma. As part of Nord Anglia's network, students access global collaborations with MIT and Juilliard. <a href="/schools/hong-kong/hong-kong/wycombe-abbey-school-hong-kong">Wycombe Abbey School Hong Kong</a> opened in 2019 in Aberdeen as one of Hong Kong's few all-girls British curriculum schools, integrating Chinese language and cultural elements alongside the English curriculum. <a href="/schools/hong-kong/hong-kong/discovery-bay-international-school">Discovery Bay International School</a> on Lantau Island serves the Discovery Bay residential community and rounds out the index at the most accessible end of the fee range.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-2xl mt-10 mb-4">Fees and debentures</h2>

        <p>
          Annual tuition for Year 3 ranges from HKD 143,500 (Discovery Bay) to HKD 264,000 (YCIS) — roughly USD 18,400 to USD 33,900 — placing Hong Kong slightly below the very top of Asia's premium tier (Shanghai and Singapore now sit higher).
        </p>

        <p>
          The critical difference in Hong Kong is debentures. Several schools require or offer debentures — one-off payments ranging from HKD 500,000 to several million. They may provide priority admission, be refundable on departure, or confer nomination rights for future students. Not all schools require them, and terms vary. Clarify the debenture position before committing.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-2xl mt-10 mb-4">What parents should know</h2>

        <p>
          Geography matters. Schools sit across Hong Kong Island (Kellett's Pok Fu Lam, German Swiss's Peak, Wycombe's Aberdeen), Kowloon (YCIS Kowloon Tong, NAIS Lam Tin), the New Territories (Harrow Tuen Mun) and Lantau (DBIS). Compute the daily commute before falling in love with a name.
        </p>

        <p>
          Pathway is the second consideration. If you want A Levels in sixth form, the index narrows to Kellett, Harrow, Wycombe Abbey, and (where available) NAIS. If you want the IB Diploma, YCIS, German Swiss, NAIS and others all run it. Co-ed versus single-sex is a factor for Wycombe Abbey, which is girls-only.
        </p>

        <p>
          Waitlists are common at the more established schools, particularly for popular year groups. Begin admissions conversations 12 months before any planned move.
        </p>

        <p>
          For a full breakdown of every school, visit the <a href="/cities/hong-kong">Hong Kong city page</a> or browse the <a href="/rankings">full rankings</a>.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </article>

  <hr class="divider container-narrow" />

  <!-- RELATED -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container-narrow">
      <p class="label mb-6">Related</p>
      <div class="flex flex-col gap-6">
        <a href="/rankings" class="font-display text-xl no-underline hover:underline" style="text-decoration:none;">
          Asia's Top British Schools — Full Rankings
        </a>
        <a href="/cities/hong-kong" class="font-display text-xl no-underline hover:underline" style="text-decoration:none;">
          Hong Kong City Guide
        </a>
        <a href="/methodology" class="font-display text-xl no-underline hover:underline" style="text-decoration:none;">
          How We Rank Schools
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <Footer slot="footer" />
</BaseLayout>
